smaller\nand surrounded by calcifications, while the false lumen is larger,\nshows delayed enhancement, and may contain \"cobwebs\"\n(collagenous media remnants).\n◦ Plain X-ray may show a widened mediastinum,\nobliteration of the aortic knuckle, or the \"calcium\nsign\" (inward displacement of atherosclerotic\ncalcification >1 cm from the aortic margin).\n86"}